title: Episode 25: The Assassination of John F. Kennedy: Part 1
description:
In an effort to win over a conservative city that he and LBJ lost in the election, John F. Kennedy visited dallas on November 23, 1963. Depsite a warm reception the fanfare was cut short when shots rang out in Dealey Plaza and JFK became the fourth President of the United States to be assassinated. There were dozens of eye witnesses but did anyone really see what happened? Or did the CIA have the wool pulled over the nation's eyes?

itunes:subtitle: November 23, 1963 is a day that will live in infamy.  In part 1 of 2 we discuss what happened that day in Dealey Plaza.  Or at least what the Warren Commission wants us to believe happened that day...
